The `getNbRows` method is asynchronous and returns a Promise that resolves to a number. Here's an example:
```
import { SimpleDB } from "@nshiab/simple-data-analysis";
// We start a SimpleDB instance
const sdb = new SimpleDB();
// We create a new table
const table = sdb.newTable();
// We load data from a file
await table.loadData("./my-data.csv");
// We get the number of rows
const nbRowsPromise = table.getNbRows();
// We await the promise to get the number of rows
const nbRows = await nbRowsPromise;
// We log the number of rows
console.log(nbRows);
// We close everything
await sdb.done();
```
